node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
We'd like to extend a big thank you to everyone that supported this year's @c2cboston clothing drive. Together we nearly doubled last year's numbers, collecting almost 500 individual pieces of donated clothing, accessories, and toys for children in need!

@mrstrillium has done the honors of selecting our five lucky $100 Gift Card raffle winners. We will be reaching out to you shortly to coordinate your prize pickup.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 10, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Today we introduce three new delightful beers to our lineup. The Pasture Series is home to unique mixed-fermentation American Wild Ales, aged in oak and thoughtfully blended to achieve well-balanced and complex drinking experiences.

Bottles of Henbit, Woolly Mullein, and Red Sorrel are now available to order for both Pickup and UPS Direct. With what's shaping up to be an absolutely gorgeous weekend, these are the beers we'll be enjoying!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Featuring the same base recipe, but different barrel selections, which present unique sensory differences in the final blends, Red Sorrel is the sibling to Woolly Mullein and rounds out our Pasture Series debut.

We highly recommend tasting it side-by-side with Woolly for a very cool look into the affects that time, distinct barrels, and blending have on a finished beer. Red Sorrel offers vibrant apricot and nectarine tones are layered upon a subtly spicy hop character and musty oak.

Bottles will become available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct. $3.55/330ml bottle, no limit per person (aside from UPS Direct state-specific limits).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of drink, outdoors and text that says 'THE HARBOR ISLAND DOUBLE IP 8%alcoholby pint brewed Massachusetts'.

node.text:
The pinnacle of our Harbor Island Series celebrates the rich history of the 34 islands and peninsulas that dot the Boston Harbor.

Hopped with a selection of some of our favorite Pacific Northwest and New Zealand varietals, this explosive Double IPA offers notes of fresh fruit salad, candied citrus, and juicy peach.

Cans of The Harbor Islands are now available for both Pickup and UPS Direct.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 08, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: As the New England weather cools, we're craving dense, buttery cake, topped with a crunchy cinnamon crumb, and a hot coffee on the side. The wait will be over soon!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 08, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Next up in our three-part Pasture Series debut is Woolly Mullein!

Featuring a simple pilsner and wheat malt base from our friends at Valley Malt, this mixed-fermentation American Wild Ale was brewed more than two years ago. After a long rest in oak, we dry-hopped with aged Slovenian hops and sent the beer off for bottle conditioning.

On Friday, it'll be ready for your enjoyment. Bottles will be available to order online for Pickup and UPS Direct. $3.55/330ml bottle, no limit per person (aside from UPS Direct state-specific limits).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and body of water.

node.text: A fresh batch of Lime Soak has returned, just in time for your end of Summer adventures. Pick up cans in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, or have them delivered to any residential address in MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, or VT!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and drink.

node.text:
This Friday, we'll introduce a new lineup of American Wild Ales: The Pasture Series.

Named after distinct pasture grasses and forbs that can be found scattered throughout the fields of the Trillium Farm in North Stonington, CT, this collection of mid-strength mixed fermentation beer utilizes distinct ingredients and processes, resulting in standalone blends that we're excited to share with you.

An American Wild Ale brewed with spelt and rye, fermented with our New England native mixed culture, and aged in oak upon a beautiful selection of herbs (lemongrass, coriander, sage, bay leaf), Henbit is one of three new offerings ready for your enjoyment.

Bottles of Henbit will be available to order online this Friday, 9/10 at 9 AM for Pickup and UPS Direct. $3.55/330ml bottle, no limit per person (aside from UPS Direct state-specific limits).

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 07, 2021. May be an image of fruit and drink.

node.text: The latest addition to the Daily Serving lineup is an absolute winner. Pairing juicy peach with vibrant mango, this palate-coating and subtly tart number will be ready for you to order online tomorrow at 9 AM. Cans will be made available for both Pickup and UPS Direct. 🥭🍑

Canton: 12-7 PM
Fenway: 12-10 PM
Fort Point: 12-7 PM

Our friends from @keanes_wood_fired will be on-site in Canton today, serving up their delicious BBQ from Noon - 5 PM. Come enjoy a beautiful finale to the holiday weekend.

node.text:
Today, two coasts, two distinct IPA traditions, and two JCs collide!

Brewed using the exact same recipe, save for one key differentiator in the yeast strain selected for fermentation, we're proud to offer two new collaboration beers with our friends at @alvaradostreetbrewery and @yakimachief.

Cans of My Name is JC (West Coast IPA) and My Name is Also JC (New England IPA), are now available to order!
